==English==

=== Etymology ===
From  [[anti-]] + [[toxin]]

=== Noun ===
'''antitoxin'''
# An [[antibody]] that is capable of neutralising specific toxins that are causative agents of disease; [[microorganism]]s including [[virus]]es and [[bacteria]]. 

